value.value: Four groups of kinases have been shown to be activated by MAP kinases, ribosomal S6 kinase (RSK also known as MAPKAPK1), MAP kinase-activated protein kinase 2/3 (MAPKAPK2/3), MAP kinase-interacting kinase or MAP kinase signal-integrating kinase (MNK) and MAPKAPK5 (PRAK).
MAPKAPK5 (PRAK) activity is regulated by p38 and activated MAPKAPK5 in turn phosphorylates small heat shock protein 27 (HSP27).
MNK1/2 are regulated by p38 and ERK, but not by JNK. MNK1/2 can phosphorylate eukaryotic initiation factor-4E (eIF-4E).
